<title>HONG KONG: Sterlite FRN increased to US$81 mln.</title>
<headline>Sterlite FRN increased to US$81 mln.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-05-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Sterlite Industries (India) Ltd's floating rate notes issue has been increased to US$81 million from US$70 million, arranger Union Bank of Switzerland Hong Kong branch said on Tuesday.</p>
<p>Priced at par, the 10-year notes have a put option after the seventh anniversay and pay a coupon of 130 basis points over the six-month London Interbank Offered Rate.</p>
<p>With fees, the all-in return for top-tier managers is 138.57 basis points.</p>
<p>Four banks joined the syndication in addition to the arranger, UBS said.</p>
<p>Signing is set for May 30, and payment for June 5.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong newsroom (852) 2843 6960</p>
